  "title": "Sustainability Specialist (Social & Partnership) | MNC Manufacturing",
  "description": "<p>The client is a global semiconductor leader, the company designs, develops, manufactures, and delivers a broad range of semiconductor products used across many industries. Below position is open urgently.</p><ul><li>Location: Ang Mo Kio</li><li>Employment Type: 12-month contract (renewable)</li><li>Working Hours: Regular Office Hours</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate local community involvement and STEM outreach programs</li><li>Engage external partners and recruit employee volunteers</li><li>Organise activities such as STEM education and digital literacy for seniors</li><li>Ensure compliance with internal processes for external engagement</li><li>Create sustainability communication content for intranet and internal platforms</li><li>Support Labour & Human Rights programs including:<br />– Social audits<br />– Meeting documentation and action tracking<br />– Development of training materials</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Sustainability, Social Sciences, Business, Communications or related fields</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Highly organised, independent and detail-oriented</li><li>Ability to manage multiple initiatives autonomously</li><li>Comfortable working with diverse stakeholders and cultures</li><li>Experience with creative tools such as Canva or video editing is a plus</li></ul><p><br /><strong>How to apply:</strong></p><p>Interested candidates, kindly email updated resume to <strong>xiaoyee@wanco-manpower.com</strong> with Subject of \"Sustainability Specialist\", thank you.</p>",
